<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3119fbd-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1784"><num value="1784">§ 1784.</num><heading> Humanitarian care</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may furnish hospital care or medical services as a humanitarian service in emergency cases, but the Secretary shall charge for such care and services at rates prescribed by the Secretary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3119fbe-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/107/135/tII/s208/b">Pub. L. 107–135, title II, § 208(b)</ref>, <date date="2002-01-23">Jan. 23, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/115/2463">115 Stat. 2463</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
